t: Out*p of the depths have I cried unto thee, O Lord.*s
Lord,*p hear my voice: let thine ears be attentive to the voice of my supplications.
If*p thou, Lord,*s shouldest mark iniquities, O Lord, who shall stand?
But*p there is forgiveness with thee, that thou mayest be feared.
I*p wait for the Lord,*s my soul doth wait, and in his word do I hope.
My*p soul waiteth for the Lord more than they that watch for the morning: I say, more than they that watch for the morning.
Let*p Israel hope in the Lord:*s for with the Lord*s there is mercy, and with him is plenteous redemption.
And*p he shall redeem Israel from all his iniquities.
